  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "An attacker can cause the Go client to allocate an arbitrary amount of memory by setting a length prefix in a byte string to a large value.\n\nThe RLP decoding function at https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/develop/rlp/decode.go#L28  looks only at the length prefix which allows for up to 256^8 sized strings; larger than available memory in computers today.\n\nFix: Add maximum size even for types which formally are unbounded. Modify the RLP decoder to reject length prefixes of larger value than can be needed for any byte array: https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/RLP#definition\n",
