    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I have thought about this for a bit.\n\nThe decoder **does** validate the size of all values against the size of an enclosing RLP list. This happens in `Stream.Kind`. It would be sufficient to only check the size of the top-level value.\n\nMost RLP is decoded from p2p messages. It would be possible to check that the top level size is not bigger than the declared size of a message there. This can be done with a single call to `Stream.Kind` before decoding the value.\n\nWe can also check the top level size in package rlp when decoding from a byte slice, which would cover most other uses.\n",
